<div id="review_2691897926" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2691897926" />
    <a title="Barbara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27456036-barbara"><img alt="Barbara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1417199404p2/27456036.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2691897926?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara" href="/user/show/27456036-barbara">Barbara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2691897926" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9549110700873177651">Sometimes, I think, great authors from the past are considered lacking in some ways. Willa Cather reminds me how well these authors could write. Her descriptions of the New Mexico and Arizona landscape were beautiful. The dedication of the two priests to their religion and the people they were devoted to was inspiring. I really enjoyed this quiet book.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


